## Risks

Medium: the distance‑preserving downstream‑travel transform (B.3.2) and the
Snell bending math (B.6) are the numerical care‑points; AC‑B3 and AC‑B6
are exact headless assertions, so floating‑point tolerance must follow the
project precedent (`MatrixComparison.fs`). The orphaning state machine (B.5)
has several edge cases (restore‑within‑distance re‑snap) that the tests must
pin precisely.

## Hand-off

Carry the baseline `gates:` YAML block forward (legacy + constructor test
counts) so `count_at_least` has a baseline. Record the public `RayModel.fs`
surface — the snap function signature, the IRG/RRG/TRG group types, the
named constants (`bundle_radius` fraction 0.4, re‑snap distance, n=1.0/1.5)
— so slice 004 (Table/Drawer/ConstructorTable) can draw the groups and
slice 005 (interaction) can wire rotation/move to re‑snapping. The visual
distinction between reflected and transmitted groups (B.6.2) is specified in
Part C (slice 004); leave it to the drawing layer.
